@startuml AgenticBenchArch
title AgentBeats Competition - Benchmark Flow\n//<color:gray>(How does evaluation work?)</color>//

skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor<<Assessee>> #E8D5F2
    BackgroundColor<<Assessor>> #C8E6C9
}

skinparam packageStyle rectangle

' High-level actors
component "Purple Agent\n(Assessee)" as Purple <<Assessee>>
component "Green Agent\n(Benchmark)" as Green <<Assessor>>

' Main benchmark flow
Purple -right-> Green : 1. narrative\n(A2A tasks/send)
Green -down-> Green : 2. evaluate\n(rules + LLM)
Green -up-> Purple : 3. evaluation\n(risk_score,\nredline)

note bottom of Purple
  **Purple Agent (Baseline)**
  ──────────────────
  • Template-based generation
  • Four-Part Test structure
  • IRS Section 41 compliance
  • A2A-compatible (:8001)
end note

note bottom of Green
  **Green Agent (Benchmark)**
  ──────────────────
  • Rule-based evaluation
  • LLM judge (optional)
  • Risk scoring (0-100)
  • Redline markup
  • A2A-compatible (:8002)
end note

@enduml
